Mode
#Parent !Root
Mode	Action
#Line
0-15	logical col = actual col
16	logical colour = RGB
17	first flash = RGB
18	second flash = RGB
24	Border colour = RGB
25	Pointer col = RGB

Add 128 to set supremacy bit.

On early machines only the top four bits of R G and B were used (for a total of 4096 available colours), and the top 4 bits had to be copied into the bottom 4 bits by the programmer to ensure the display would remain the same on a 16M colour (24-bit) system.
